ZH: 他在压低阀门以减少压力。
EN: He is lowering the valve to reduce the pressure.

ZH: 这个机器能够自动压低音量。
EN: This machine can automatically lower the volume.

ZH: 她压低声音，小心地告诉了他一个秘密。
EN: She lowered her voice and carefully told him a secret.

ZH: 为了保持安全，他压低了电子设备的亮度。
EN: For safety reasons, he lowered the brightness of the electronic devices.

ZH: 我们需要压低音乐，以便能够谈论。
EN: We need to lower the music so that we can talk.

ZH: 他压低了汽车的悬挂以适应不平的道路。
EN: He lowered the suspension of the car to adapt to the uneven road.

ZH: 在夜间，他们压低灯光以避免刺眼。
EN: During the night, they lowered the lights to avoid glare.

ZH: 压低成本意味着降低质量。
EN: Lowering costs means reducing quality.

ZH: 他们要压低价格来吸引更多顾客。
EN: They want to lower the price to attract more customers.

ZH: 她的手艺压低了其他竞争者。
EN: Her skills overshadowed other competitors.

ZH: 这个国家的治安压低了游客的兴趣。
EN: The country's security situation lowered the interest of tourists.

ZH: 他压低头，意识到自己犯了一个错误。
EN: He lowered his head, realizing that he had made a mistake.

ZH: 压低木材价格会影响到伐木业。
EN: Lowering timber prices will affect the logging industry.

ZH: 这个岛屿的气候压低了人们的生活质量。
EN: The climate of this island lowers the quality of life for the people.

